        "job_name": "Eliminate a corrupt magnate",
        "job_description": "A blacked-out figure with a synthesized voice shows up in a recording:\n\"$name is smart, $heSheThey created an impressive new technology that could help create ==spaceborne farms== for colonies struggling with pollution or lackluster farmland and light. ^$heIsSheIsTheyAre also incredibly greedy and cunning. ^$heSheThey managed to charm, bribe, and threaten enough higher-ups in the corporation to fund $hisHerTheir little experiment at full scale while reaping all of its benefits.\"\nThe shadowy figure ponders for a second.\n\"While the Tritachyon Corporation encourages its employees to always be on the lookout for these leaps of innovation, sometimes at the expense of colleagues, several senior board members such as myself understand that the most egregious schemes must be discouraged. There is one golden rule within our corporation: ==Never defraud the company!==\"\nThe shadowy figure let this implied threat linger for just a little longer than necessary as if it was going to be relevant to the mission.\n\"Long story short, $name made a few more enemies than $heSheThey should. $heSheThey has already refused to leave $hisHerTheir fleet and come down to testify in front of the board, sending a regiment of lawyers instead. I do not think $firstName has quite realized how much trouble $heIsSheIsTheyAre in: we will not stand idly by while $heSheThey attempts to indefinitely delay $hisHerTheir fall. You are hereby ==mandated to arrest $name==, and deliver $himHerThem to us. Should $heSheThey resist, you are ==authorized any level of force necessary to either capture or stop $himHerThem indefinitely.== Damages to $hisHerTheir ship are acceptable as long as the mission gets carried out. However ==it must be delivered to us too==. Good hunting captain.\"",
        "job_comm_reply": "After several attemps at deflecting your request from $hisHerTheir comm officer, you are finally put in contact with $name. As expected given your orders, $heSheThey flatly refuses to step out of $hisHerTeir ship. Fortunately, your unambiguous mandate leaves little room for \"scheduling conflicts\", \"health concerns\" and other such excuses.\nFinally understanding that you are not going anywhere without $himHerThem, $heSheThey changes $hisHerTheir approach:\n\"Excuse me, but I do not see a name on this warrant, only \"the board of directors\". I do not dispute this is an authentic notice, but I'm wondering under whose authority it was released. Artemisia Sun and her inner circle aren't known for playing subtle shadowy games when it comes to internal affairs, yet you claim to be acting on behalf of the whole board. Are you certain you are playing for the big guys and are not a pawn in a ploy to take down a legitimate director for someone else's profit? Why use a free agent at all? It's not like the company lacks a military force!\"\n^&heSheThey pauses for a second to let you time to process the argument.\n\"You know how it works around here. Henchmen don't last long when they are on the wrong team.\"\nThe diversion is obvious, yet you cannot say for sure it did not work.",
        "job_intel_success": "As the $shipName collapses you immediately send a boarding shuttle to try and capture $name, or at least confirm $hisHerTheir demise. Your team quickly makes their way to the bridge, but $firstName is nowhere to be found. You suspect fool's play and ask your team to comb over the sensors recording from the moment you approached the fleet.\nJust as you presumed, they notice a shuttle departing right before the battle begins. Fortunately, it limited its thrust to keep its signature low and after some quick calculations, your tactical team locates it.\nA second boarding team is able to quickly secure the target, and deliver $himHerThem at the requested location. Nary a word is exchanged, but the reward is immediately transferred to your account.",
        "job_intel_failure": "You are probably making some powerful enemies for yourself, but this ship is a money-printing machine. No wonder some board members were miffed at $name for keeping all the profits for $himslefHerselfThemselves.\nYour team was able to locate his shuttle far from the battle: as expected from such egotistical genius, being in danger is not a thrilling experience $heIsSheIsTheyAre fond of and $heSheThey left the ship long before the shooting started. Hopefully $hisHerTheir delivery will smooth things over a little bit with your client.",
