        "job_name": "Face the Remnant abomination",
        "job_description": "This is a mission posted in a newsletter from a non-profit organization centered around public concern about the Remnant threat. While technically not very influential, they have a thin but dedicated support base on all colonies in the sector. Furthermore, they have unofficial Luddic Church backing, probably as a way to keep the danger of AIs alive in everyone's mind.\n\"==THE REMNANT MENACE GROWS==\nThe scheming AIs have started the next step in their bit to eliminate humanity from the sector. Exclusive witness reports acquired by our organization have revealed that a new AI machine of war has been built. One ==more frightening than the dreaded Radiant==.\"\n[...]\n\"Only grit and cunning allowed these brave men and women to escape the deadly claws of this trap. You will find the frightening accounts of their encounter on page 6!\"\n[...]\n\"It is time that we, as an organization, take a stand against the scourge of AIs. We cannot let exploration fleets and other salvagers face this threat alone. Now is the moment for a decisive campaign aimed at the heart of the enemy. We have asked for your generous donations time and time again, and you have answered our calls. We are now ready to announce to the world that there is a massive ==$reward cedits reward== for the heroes able to defeat this monstrosity.\"\nThe newsletter keeps on for several paragraphs about the glorious future of those shining heroes, as well as several legal disclaimers and no-responsibility clauses.",
        "job_intel_success": "You receive an immediate reply to your victory report. Visibly keen to capitalize on this event, the organization heads want to schedule several interviews at a ridiculous pace and to secure exclusive rights to the story. Along come several lawyers' letters with contracts and royalties agreements. It takes you but a glance at those terms to determine they can at best be described as insulting. What is conspicuously missing though, is your agreed-upon monetary reward.\n\nFortunately, this is nothing that thinly veiled threats, both legal and otherwise, cannot solve. The missing credits promptly materialize in your account.",
		"job_intel_failure": "Your client will definitely not like this, but you are pretty proud of your catch. Actually you can't believe you were able to pull that salvage up; Ludd or someone else must be looking after you to make it at all possible. Now hopefully nothing bad will ever come from using such a cursed ship in your fleet.",
        "job_intel_expired": "Your intelligence officer sends you a memo about this bounty. It seems that the organization that posted the offer is in a bit of turmoil after the account for the reward money was found empty. It is unclear if this is the doing of a disgruntled former member, a hacking, or plain misappropriation, but one thing is certain: nobody is getting paid for the destruction of that \"AI abomination\". It is probably still present in the $system system though.",
