		"job_name": "Settling a bet",
        "job_description": "This is an odd job: ostensibly not a serious offer, yet its content is puzzling.\nYou watch the amateur recording of the ramblings from a distressed, and visibly quite inebriated, sailor about a ==tragic encounter in the outer reaches== of the sector. While barely coherent, they had garnered a small gathering of various bar-goers riveted by their story.\nYou cannot make out everything clearly but they are describing a ==gigantic Derelict drone== unlike any other that the salvager team accidentally \"woke up\". It would then start ==reactivating other regular drones to form an armada==. There are also allusions to a ==red eye==, of disappearing boarding parties, and of \"random machinery turning on against their users\" within the fleet. The story ends with only a few survivors fleeing the system after ==the drone opened fire on the fleet with its gigantic cannon==.\nFollowing the recording are excerpts of the reactions and speculations from virtual forum users. Some praised the acting of such an obviously made-up scenario, others mentioned the existence of conspicuously similar rumors and urban legends. You skim over long arguments about the plausibility of a surviving derelict drone still operational enough to reactivate others.\nThe last part of the post covers two of the most virulent forum-goers ==setting up a $reward bet== about whether there is some grain of truth to the sailor's story.",
        "job_intel_success": "Out of curiosity, you decide to post the recordings of the battle on the same virtual forums that used to discuss the sailor's story. As expected, it causes quite a whirlwind of activity. Lots of consternation and concerns that such a thing could exist, lots of speculating and theory-crafting on how it could have come to be. You also receive a lot of praise for the computer-generated visual effects in this \"fictional short movie\", as well as criticism for the \"less realistic parts\".\n\nThe promised $reward credits do get eventually transferred to your account, so there is that.",
        "job_intel_failure": "You accomplished the impossible and captured the drone, legendary tales will be told about this feat! The AI themselves will tremble in fear of your mighty power...\n\nAnd yet deep down, you understand what a travesty this is.",
        "job_intel_expired": "After two cycles and nothing of substance to add to the debate, the bet has been settled in favor of the \"doubt\" camp. If there is anything in the $system system, it must still be there.",
		"job_deadline": 3600,
