		"job_name": "Venturing into the forbidden zone",
        "job_description": "A strange offer catches your attention. There is no clearly defined goal or target but a series of speculations derived from a patchwork of articles and official military reports.\n==[DECENAL THREAT REPORT CLAIMS SPACE HAS NEVER BEEN SAFER]==\nThe article claims that only piracy poses a significant menace, but denotes a few hotspots of AI activity to avoid.\n==[INSURANCE PRICES ON THE RISE FOR PROSPECTORS]==\nThis highlights a string of dramatic losses from a couple of large scavenger organizations. Those deaths were pinned on a possible Remnant stronghold.\n==[ARE THE REMNANTS OF THE SECOND AI WAR TO BLAME?]==\nA very public colonization attempt had failed, with no survivor and only wreckages to tell a puzzling story.\n[WHERE ARE THE MISSING SHIPS?]\nAn investigative journalist had noted some discrepancies between the official Tri-Tachyon fleet numbers, their recorded losses, and their public military budget. The revelation of a possible hidden force caused quite a stir then, but the whole affair died down after \"secret\" talks between the major powers.\n==[FAMILIES ASK FOR REPARATION]==\nThe Persean League had shuffled around a lot of personnel and made liberal use of \"operational security\" to hide multiple ship losses that occurred sometime between 168 and 170. Facing rising anger among their citizens, they had to admit having suffered a major defeat at the hand of an unspecified opponent. If it was Remnant or Derelict drones why just not say it? What if it was not either of those?\n==[HEGEMONY ROUTINE INSPECTIONS ARE GETTING OUT OF HAND]==\nThat's it, that's the smoking gun: this report lists all the overzealous inspections from Hegemony patrols during the cycles 173 to 178. They were seven times as likely to stop prospector fleets headed for that one quadrant of the sector than anywhere else. They were trying to keep something hidden from the public!\nThe post goes on, and on, and on, tying seemingly unrelated events into one big conspiracy. The author narrowed the location of this supposed forbidden zone, or rather \"current location\" as they explain it changed place from time to time, somehow. This is all pretty close to wild speculations but the author did put some money where their mouth was. They must be certain there is something to find out there.",
        "job_intel_success": "You send your client all the data you have about the encounter. A few hours pass before you get a reply: the reward is there, along with a massive document demanding additional information, and several hundred multiple-choice questions. The whole thing was visibly written in a rush and barely legible, between the wild excitement and exaggerated highlights. You discard the document and tell your communication officer to ignore any further communication from that character.\n\nMeanwhile your engineers are asking for an emergency meeting to discuss safety procedures if the fleet is to face another of these ships bearing their \"nano-machine plague\".",
        "job_intel_failure": "You stare at the hulk while your crew works miracles to bring it back online. Nobody expected this to be even possible but your engineering team had one very special ace up their sleeve.",
        "job_intel_expired": "Your intelligence officer informs you about the cancellation of the job offer, and that the client's account cannot be found anymore. That is quite strange, nearly unheard of even. You wonder what could have led the job board management to take such action. Is it possible the conspiracies were true? Either way, whatever might be out there can still be found.",
