		"job_description": "Terrorists have stolen from us a valuable but dangerous artifact from the Domain. Despite our efforts to keep this vessel existence a secret, they managed to breach our hidden Hyperspace Research Facilities, embark on the ship, and depart to the fringe. We have no idea if their intention is to sell it to the highest bidder or to turn it against us, but in either case the ship is dangerous and must be destroyed.\nI would personally prefer that the Persean Council is never made aware of this incident, or the existence of this ship, thus this rather unconventional note.",
		"job_comm_reply": "As the communication is established, the screen suddenly shows a Pather officer already in the middle of their sermon. You cannot tell if they are animated by a fiery passion, or putting up an act and enjoying it:\n\"...Shall not take this cursed artefact from our care. It shall be delivered to our high priests and they will decide whether it can be cleansed from the curse of the Gates, or if it must be reduced to atoms and dispersed to the hyper-space winds. Begone heathen! Do not stand in the way of this holy endeavor! I shall enforce...\"\nYou cut the communication before getting a headache.",
