		"job_name": "Ruining the parade",
		"job_description": "The Navy of ==$location== has somehow managed to restore an old ==Quicksilver-class battlecruiser prototype== into working condition. Records about that ship are spotty at best but all indicate that such an asset could significantly disrupt the balance of powers in the region, which makes other nearby independent governments anxious. Furthermore, given the costs associated with restoring and deploying this ship in combat, it is not excluded that the good governor of $location received financial backings from a third party with their own motivations./nIn any case this ship's destruction has been deemed necessary and funds have been allocated for a reward. Fortunately, the ship has been revealed during a military parade and will be extremely exposed while touring the ==$system system== for the next few weeks.\nPlease note that no \"Lettre de marque\" will be provided as to not further disrupt the current unstable geopolitical landscape.",
		"job_comm_reply": "On the screen appears an officer whose uniform would not have been out of place for a villain in a cheesy holovid. They puff their chest and a mosaic of gold medals cause all kinds of flares that the camera is unable to mitigate, then erupt in a comically authoritative voice.\n\"Attention incoming vessels, this is the Admiral $name speaking. I order you to turn around and leave the system of face an immediate obliteration. The $faction Fleet will not tolerate any encroachment on our territory. This mighty ship can turn your puny hulls to dust in a snap of my fingers...\"\nOne of your officers cannot contain a burst of restrained laughter and the whole CIC starts to grin and smirk. You order to cut the feed before everyone loses their concentration right before the battle.",
